oc:kn_0c914608 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning extraction scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Design systems grow incrementally. Extract what's clearly reusable now, not everything that might someday be reusable." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incremental extraction keeps the system focused, maintainable, and aligned with actual project needs." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_16ce3f35 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, before starting any extraction work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before extraction, locate the design system via grep for 'design system', 'ui', 'components', and understand its organization, naming conventions, token structure, documentation patterns, and import/export conventions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Understanding existing conventions ensures new extractions integrate seamlessly rather than creating inconsistencies." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_18167556 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After replacing existing uses with shared versions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "After migration, verify visual and functional parity, then delete dead code from old implementations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ensures the refactoring didn't introduce regressions and removes stale code that could confuse future developers." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7bada6f6 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assessing whether to extract a pattern" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Extract patterns only when used 3+ times or likely to be reused, systematizing improves consistency, the pattern is general not context-specific, and maintenance cost justifies the benefit." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premature extraction wastes effort and creates maintenance burden for patterns that never get reused." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_82a3a154 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting components and tokens" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never extract one-off, context-specific implementations without generalization. Never create components so generic they're useless. Never skip TypeScript types or prop documentation. Never create tokens for every single value — tokens should have semantic meaning." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-extraction clutters the design system; under-extraction defeats its purpose. Both extremes reduce the system's value." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e8b2da5e a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When discovering the project's design system structure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If no design system exists, ask before creating one. Understand the preferred location and structure first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Creating a design system without alignment on conventions leads to conflicting patterns and poor adoption." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

